Deji Adeyanju, a well- known Nigerian activist, claims that the All Progressives Congress’ s (APC) presidential ticket for 2023 will go to the South- South, Daily Trust report.
Adeyanju made the allegation on his Twitter page on Thursday, where he divulged astounding details regarding the future APC presidential candidate.
Adeyanju stated the APC is considering handing its presidential ticket to an Igbo candidate beside photos of Rotimi Amaechi and Godwin Emefiele.
According to Adeyanju, sources within the APC have informed him that the presidential ticket for 2023 will be refused to Asiwaju Tinubu and Yemi Osinbajo’ s camp.
” The APC presidential ticket is likely to go to the South- South, and the advantage that both have is that they are Igbo guys, ” the tweet said.
According to numerous APC sources, the South West will not get it. You heard it first from the ThiefNubu and Osinbajo camps, who will mourn and cry. ”
Former President Goodluck Jonathan, according to Adeyanju, has a better chance of winning the presidential election than Tinubu.
” In APC, they’ re going to show the ThiefNubu’ Tinubu pepper. ” He tweeted, ” Goodluck Jonathan has a better chance of earning an APC ticket than he does. ”
Remember that Kaduna State Governor Nasir El Rufai stated that the APC presidential candidate would come from the south.
The Governor stated that it is up to the APC’ s southern caucus to pick which section of the state the presidential candidate will represent.
On March 26th, the APC will hold its national convention.
