According to another report, the northern faction supports Amaechi as Buhari’ s successor.
The Coalition of Northern Youth for Good Governance has backed Rotimi Amaechi, the Minister of Transportation, to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari (retd) in 2023.
According to the group, Amaechi, who is 56 years old, is free of the old age- related health issues that some aspirants face.
The group’ s National Coordinator, Bilal Dakiyak, told journalists in Abuja on Monday that Amaechi is the finest guy to keep President Buhari’ s momentum of diversification and economic transformation going.
He urged Amaechi, on the other hand, to make an official declaration of his intention to run for the country’ s top post as soon as possible.
”The process for selecting and ultimately electing this successor in the 2023 General Elections is already underway, ” he stated.
”The Coalition of Northern Youth for Good Governance prefers that the All Progressive Congress continue in office for the sake of continuity. ”
”As a result, Nigeria would not experience losses as a result of different political parties’ governments deciding not to carry out the programs and initiatives initiated by the previous administration. ”
It is well documented that Nigeria has suffered greatly due to a lack of government continuity. Tambuwal adds, ” I’ ll begin consultations on the presidency in 2023. ”
”As a result, we have rigorously evaluated the outstanding Nigerians who have expressed an interest in running for President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, and we have decided on the Honourable Minister of Transport, Mr. Rotimi Amaechi.






